# DOM Runtime

## Source Files

Source is plain JavaScript (no build step). Files are consumed directly by downstream bundlers, enabling tree-shaking.

- `client.js` — Client-side DOM rendering, hydration, event delegation
- `server.js` — SSR streaming, asset tracking, serialization
- `universal.js` — `createRenderer()` factory for non-DOM platforms
- `reconcile.js` — Array reconciliation algorithm (based on udomdiff)
- `constants.js` — DOM/SVG element sets, delegated events, property mappings
- `serializer.js` — `seroval`-based serializer for SSR data hydration

## `rxcore` Imports

All modules import reactive primitives from `"rxcore"`. This is rewritten at consume time — never add a real `rxcore` dependency. Client imports: `root`, `effect`, `memo`, `getOwner`, `createComponent`, `sharedConfig`, `untrack`, `mergeProps`, `flatten`. Server adds: `ssrHandleError`, `ssrRunInScope`.

## Client Patterns

- `template(html, count)` — creates a `<template>` element, caches it, returns clones. `count` indicates expected child count for normalization.
- `insert(parent, accessor, marker, initial)` — core insertion. Wraps reactive accessors in `effect()`. Handles strings, numbers, nodes, arrays, and functions.
- `spread(node, props, skipChildren)` — applies a dynamic props object to a DOM element. Handles style objects, classList, event listeners, refs, and attributes.
- `delegateEvents(eventNames)` — attaches a single listener per event type to `document`. Events are dispatched via `_$DX_DELEGATE` property on nodes.
- `render(code, element)` — entry point. Creates a reactive root and inserts into the target element.

## Hydration

Key-based hydration via `sharedConfig.registry`. `getNextElement()` walks the DOM to find matching elements by `data-hk` attribute. `runHydrationEvents()` replays events captured during SSR.

## SSR Patterns

- `renderToString()` / `renderToStream()` — entry points with `RequestContext` for shared state
- `ssr()` — tagged template helper that concatenates SSR output
- Asset tracking via `createAssetTracking()` — manages boundary-scoped CSS/JS assets
- Fragment boundaries use comment markers (`<!--!$-->`, `<!--/-->`)

## Style / Class Handling

`style(node, value, prev)` and `className(node, value)` handle both string and object forms. Style objects diff property-by-property. CSS custom properties use `setProperty()`; standard properties use direct assignment.
